🧠 1. Can You Use “Areas We Serve” + “Services” Sections?

✅ YES — and you should
But they need to be intentional, not generic.

⸻

🔥 The Right Way to Use Them

On: /airport-limo-toronto

✅ “Areas We Serve” (horizontal linking — SAME SERVICE)

This should link to:
 • Airport Limo Mississauga
 • Airport Limo Brampton
 • Airport Limo Vaughan

👉 NOT just “Mississauga” (important)

<h3>Airport Limo Services in Nearby Cities</h3>
<a href="/airport-limo-mississauga">Mississauga Airport Limo</a>
<a href="/airport-limo-brampton">Brampton Airport Limo</a>


⸻

✅ “Our Services” (vertical linking — SAME CITY)

This should link to:
 • Wedding Limo Toronto
 • Corporate Limo Toronto
 • Prom Limo Toronto

<h3>Our Limo Services in Toronto</h3>
<a href="/wedding-limo-toronto">Wedding Limo Toronto</a>
<a href="/corporate-limo-toronto">Corporate Limo Toronto</a>


⸻

⚠️ MOST IMPORTANT RULE

❗ Anchor text must match the page

Bad:

<a href="/airport-limo-mississauga">Mississauga</a>

Good:

<a href="/airport-limo-mississauga">Mississauga Airport Limo</a>

👉 This is a huge SEO difference

⸻

🧠 2. Is This Enough Alone?

👉 Almost — but not fully

To really make it strong, you ALSO want:

✅ 1–2 contextual links inside content

Example:

We also provide <a href="/corporate-limo-toronto">corporate limo services in Toronto</a> for business clients.

👉 This adds semantic relevance, not just structural links

⸻

🧠 3. Do You Need Hub Pages?

🔥 YES — but ONLY 1 per service

You need:

/airport-limo
/wedding-limo
/corporate-limo

These are your main hubs

⸻

❌ You do NOT need city hubs like:

/toronto-limo-services   ❌ (optional, not required)
/mississauga-limo       ❌

Unless you’re going very advanced.

⸻

🧠 Why Service Hubs Matter

They:
 • Connect ALL city pages
 • Give Google a top-level page to rank
 • Pass authority down

⸻

Example: /airport-limo

<h2>Airport Limo Services</h2>

<a href="/airport-limo-toronto">Toronto Airport Limo</a>
